Who knew a humble apple could double as a great craft item? While apples are good for kids to eat, as they contain antioxidants, vitamins, dietary fiber, and a range of other nutrients, they’re also perfect shaped for stamping. Anything that allows children to get their hands dirty and interact with their food is a winning mix. So today, we’re going to show you how to have stamping fun with an apple, paint, paper, and a little imagination. 